description: For nine days, waves of pro-democracy protests engulfed Hong Kong, swelling at times to tens of thousands of people and raising tensions with Beijing.
title: Images of Hong Kong’s Umbrella Revolution
title_page: Images of Hong Kong’s Umbrella Revolution - The New York Times
maintext: Pro-democracy demonstrators began pulling back on their blockade of the offices of Hong Kong’s leader on Sunday and debated whether to abandon another key encampment as the government set a Monday morning deadline for the police to restore access to the government’s headquarters.
